`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The `placeModularPiece` tests use three key patterns working together:
1. **Minimal mock interfaces** (`KitbashPlacementWorld`, `KitbashCommitStore`) — defined in the production code with exactly the methods tests need to spy on, avoiding any real store/ECS setup.
2. **Atomic pre-check test** — the "does not spend any resource if only the second resource is insufficient" test verifies the two-phase commit pattern (check-all, then spend-all), which prevents partial resource deduction.
3. **`makeGroundedRapier()` helper** — consolidates the common happy-path Rapier mock (clear + grounded) so each test can override only the one dimension under test.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
